A for loop is used when you want to repeat something a certain number of times.
EXAMPLE:
  if you want to print n times which means you know the value fo n .
  do it 5  times and print hello 5 times .
  start from 1 and end at 10.

Syntax:
for (initialization; condition; update) {
    // Code to repeat
}

Program:
  public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}
output:
  1
  2
  3
  4
  5

public static void my(){
        int number=10;
        System.out.println("EVEN NUMBERS ");
        for(int i=0;i<=number;i=i+2){
            System.out.println(i);
        }
}
public static void loop(){
        int[] mark={81,71,78,69,75,72};
        for(int i=0;i<mark.length;i++){
            System.out.println("SUBJECT "+(i+1)+" :"+ mark[i]);
        }
    }
}

NOTE : you can use for loop for executing many things at once one by one.
